com.tibco.xpd.customer.api.iprocess.amxbpm.conversion

Class AbstractIProcessToBPMContribution

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tibco.xpd.customer.api.iprocess.amxbpm.conversion.AbstractIProcessToBPMContribution

  • public abstract class AbstractIProcessToBPMContribution
extends Object
    This class is the required contribution for the com.tibco.xpd.customer.api.iProcessBpmConversion extension point that allows pluggable contribution to the TIBCO iProcess To AMX BPM XPDL Conversion Framework for individual, discreet conversion tasks of TIBCO iProcess processes into TIBCO AMX BPM processes.

    The contributor class must implement the convert(List, List, IProgressMonitor) method during which modifications can be made to the processes being converted. One instance of each life-cycle listener contribution is created per-conversion use case (i.e. for each batch of XPDLs selected for import/conversion by the user).

    Only the TIBCO-owned data and classes used or returned directly or indirectly by the above class are considered public API.
    Any other data, class or extension point contained with TIBCO-owned features and plug-ins outside of the com.tibco.xpd.customer.api feature and plug-in must be considered internal and private to TIBCO and are subject to change without notice.

    Access is provided to the required Eclipse Modelling Framework (EMF) model packages and factories that provide Java-Based representations of the XPDL and TIBCO extension models, see...

    • getXpdlFactory()
    • getXpdExtensionPackage() and getXpdExtensionFactory()
    • getIProcessExtPackage() and getIProcessExtFactory()
    • getEmailPackage() and getEmailFactory()
    • getDatabasePackage() and getDatabaseFactory()
    • getEaijavaPackage() and getEaijavaPackage()

    Helper methods for getting and setting extension model elements on base XPDL elements are provided, ,see..

    • getExtensionAttribute(OtherAttributesContainer, EStructuralFeature)
    • getExtensionElement(OtherElementsContainer, EStructuralFeature)
    • setExtensionAttribute(OtherAttributesContainer, EStructuralFeature, Object)
    • setExtensionElement(OtherElementsContainer, EStructuralFeature, Object)

    For further information on the iProcess to AMX BPM Conversion Framework, the com.tibco.xpd.customer.api.iProcessBpmConversion extension point and also guidance on the use of the XPDL process models and extension models, please see the extension point documentation.

    Copyright (c) TIBCO Software Inc 2004 - 2014. All rights reserved.

    Since:
    TIBCO Business Studio BPM Edition v3.8

    • Method Detail

      • convert

        public abstract org.eclipse.core.runtime.IStatus convert(List<com.tibco.xpd.xpdl2.Process> processes,
                                       List<com.tibco.xpd.xpdExtension.ProcessInterface> processInterfaces,
                                       org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor monitor)
        This is the main entry point function for the contribution.

        Perform an necessary modifications to the list of processes / process interfaces being converted.

        Parameters:
        processes - The list of processes being converted.
        processInterfaces - The list of process interfaces being converted.
        monitor - Standard Eclipse monitor for progress status updates (see IProgressMonitor for more information. This method should call at least monitor.beginTask() at the start of the method and monitor.done() at the end. The conversion framework will have already pre-loaded the progress status with your contributions description. To overwrite the progress status message completely, use both monitor.setTaskname(String) and monitor.subTask(string).
        Returns:
        IStatus representing the outcome of the conversion process. IStatus.OK is the nominal return, Istatus.INFO / WARNING can be used to return information messages (that will be logged with debug mode switched on). IStatus.ERROR status will stop the conversion process and report the error.Use ImportDisplayStatus status type for messages to be displayed to the user at the end of the complete conversion of the XPDL.For more details see ImportDisplayStatus

      • getConverterContributionsInfo

        public static Collection<ConversionContributionInfo> getConverterContributionsInfo()
        Information class detailing individual contributions to the com.tibco.xpd.customer.api.iProcessBpmConversion extension point.

        This is provided to allow customer extension developers to see all contributions' OrderingPriority, ConverterId and ConversionDescription values. This my be useful when a customer extension developer wishes to insert conversions before or after particular base, generic Business Studio-provided conversion contributions.

        Returns:
        The unmodifiable collection of com.tibco.xpd.customer.api.iProcessBpmConversion contributions that are currently contributed to the underlying TIBCO Business Studio BPM Edition version.

      • getExistingProcess

        protected com.tibco.xpd.xpdl2.Process getExistingProcess(com.tibco.xpd.xpdl2.Process conversionProcess)
        Retrieve the equivalent, already converted, version of the given process for conversion from the Business Studio workspace if it exists.

        Sub-processes should normally be included included in the project set for conversion of each main process. Therefore these sub-processes may already have been converted into AMX BPM processes and even been edited by the user. Such processes are still included in the original set for conversion but will be stripped out prior to final save of resources (in order to prevent overwrite of existing modified copies in the users workspace).

        The equivalence is based upon the Process name.

        Parameters:
        conversionProcess - Process from the conversion set to check
        Returns:
        Existing equivalent, already converted, version of the given process for conversion from the Business Studio workspace if one exists or null if no such equivalent process exists.

      • getExistingProcessInterface

        protected com.tibco.xpd.xpdExtension.ProcessInterface getExistingProcessInterface(com.tibco.xpd.xpdExtension.ProcessInterface conversionProcessIFC)
        Retrieve the equivalent, already converted, version of the given process interface (iProcess I/O Template) for conversion from the Business Studio workspace if it exists.

        iProcess I/O Templates should normally be included included in the project set for conversion of each main process. Therefore these I/O templates may already have been converted into AMX BPM process interfaces and even been edited by the user. Process interfaces are still included in the original set for conversion but will be stripped out prior to final save of resources (in order to prevent overwrite of existing modified copies in the users workspace).

        The equivalence is based upon the ProcessInterface name.

        Parameters:
        conversionProcessInterface - ProcessInterface from the conversion set to check
        Returns:
        Existing equivalent, already converted, version of the given process interface for conversion from the Business Studio workspace if one exists or null if no such equivalent process interface exists.

      • getExtensionAttribute

        protected final Object getExtensionAttribute(com.tibco.xpd.xpdl2.OtherAttributesContainer xpdlElement,
                           org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EStructuralFeature extensionFeature)
        Retrieve the value of an extension model attribute from the given XPDL element.

        • Each model extension top-level attribute or element is declared as a child feature of the DocumentRoot element and its identification is accessed via the EMF Package Java class for the extension model.
        • This feature identifier allows EMF to identify a particular model feature amongst the many that can be added to any ##other capable XPDL model element.
        • For example the xpdExt:DisplayName attribute is declared in the XpdExtension schema.
        • The schema model features are represented by the com.tibco.xpd.xpdExtension.XpdExtensionPackage class.
        • And therefore the feature identifier for this extension attribute accessible via this class as the method XpdExtensionPackage.getDocumentRoot_DisplayName()


        The EMF Packages for each of the extension models is available from the following methods...

        • AbstractIProcessToBPMContribution.getXpdExtensionPackage() - gets the EMF package for the Studio generic and AMX BPM extensions (http://www.tibco.com/XPD/xpdExtension1.0.0) model
        • AbstractIProcessToBPMContribution.getIProcessExtPackage() - gets the EMF package for the Studio iProcess extensions (http://www.tibco.com/XPD/iProcessExt1.0.0) model
        • AbstractIProcessToBPMContribution.getEmailPackage() - gets the EMF package for the Email Service Task extensions (http://www.tibco.com/XPD/email1.0.0) model
        • AbstractIProcessToBPMContribution.getDatabasePackage() - gets the EMF package for the Database Service Task extensions (http://www.tibco.com/XPD/database1.0.0) model
        • AbstractIProcessToBPMContribution.getEaijavaPackage() - gets the EMF package for the Java Service Task extensions (http://www.tibco.com/XPD/EAIJava1.0.0) model



        Parameters:
        xpdlElement - The element on which the extension attribute is set (EMF classes for XPDL element types that support ##other construct will implement the OtherAttributesContainer interface required for this parameter).
        extensionFeature - The extension model DocumentRoot feature identification from the appropriate EMF package for the extension attribute.
        Returns:
        The extension attribute if defined, or null if not.

      • setExtensionAttribute

        protected final void setExtensionAttribute(com.tibco.xpd.xpdl2.OtherAttributesContainer xpdlElement,
                         org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EStructuralFeature extensionFeature,
                         Object value)
        Sets the given extension attribute feature to the given value on the given XPDL element.

        • Each model extension top-level attribute or element is declared as a child feature of the DocumentRoot element and its identification is accessed via the EMF Package Java class for the extension model.
        • This feature identifier allows EMF to identify a particular model feature amongst the many that can be added to any ##other capable XPDL model element.
        • For example the xpdExt:DisplayName attribute is declared in the XpdExtension schema.
        • The schema model features are represented by the com.tibco.xpd.xpdExtension.XpdExtensionPackage class.
        • And therefore the feature identifier for this extension attribute accessible via this class as the method XpdExtensionPackage.getDocumentRoot_DisplayName()


        The EMF Packages for each of the extension models is available from the following methods...

        • AbstractIProcessToBPMContribution.getXpdExtensionPackage() - gets the EMF package for the Studio generic and AMX BPM extensions (http://www.tibco.com/XPD/xpdExtension1.0.0) model
        • AbstractIProcessToBPMContribution.getIProcessExtPackage() - gets the EMF package for the Studio iProcess extensions (http://www.tibco.com/XPD/iProcessExt1.0.0) model
        • AbstractIProcessToBPMContribution.getEmailPackage() - gets the EMF package for the Email Service Task extensions (http://www.tibco.com/XPD/email1.0.0) model
        • AbstractIProcessToBPMContribution.getDatabasePackage() - gets the EMF package for the Database Service Task extensions (http://www.tibco.com/XPD/database1.0.0) model
        • AbstractIProcessToBPMContribution.getEaijavaPackage() - gets the EMF package for the Java Service Task extensions (http://www.tibco.com/XPD/EAIJava1.0.0) model



        Parameters:
        xpdlElement - The element on which the extension attribute is set (EMF classes for XPDL element types that support ##other construct will implement the OtherAttributesContainer interface required for this parameter).
        extensionFeature - The extension model DocumentRoot feature identification from the appropriate EMF package for the extension attribute.
        value - The value of the attribute to set or null to unset the element. It is the caller's responsibility to ensure that the value is of the appropriate type for the given feature. Failure to do so will not cause an error during set but will cause unexpected behaviour and exceptions in code that reads this model attribute later.

        Parameters:
        xpdlElement - The element on which the extension element is set (EMF classes for XPDL element types that support ##other construct will implement the OtherAttributesContainer interface required for this parameter).
        extensionFeature - The extension model DocumentRoot feature identification from the appropriate EMF package for the extension element.
        value - The value of the element to set or null to unset the element. It is the caller's responsibility to ensure that the value is of the appropriate type for the given feature. Failure to do so will not cause an error during set but will cause unexpected behaviour and exceptions in code that reads this model element later.
